&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hi, we’re Supergoop! Since 2005, we’ve been changing the way the world thinks about sunscreen. Today, we’re as committed as ever to creating feel-good sunscreen that you’ll really want to wear. Because protecting your skin’s health is what we’re all about. Every. Single. Day.™&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Analyst, Demand Planning, you will bring your collaborative nature and analytical skills to regularly prepare and review forecasts and demand plans to ensure Supergoop!’s product supply is available at levels able to meet our consumer demands, while using your creative problem-solving approach to manage inventory concerns.&amp;nbsp; Working cross-functionally with internal teams, you will be primarily responsible for&amp;nbsp;development and maintenance of plans and reports, analyzing sales data and trends, and communicating with cross-functional partners on inventory and supply chain related matters. In this role you will report directly to the Demand Planner.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzing sales data, trends, and customer behavior to create demand plans. Manage escalation process for changes to demand plan inside lead time. Ensure new product launch demand is supported by comparative product launch and sell-through information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage inventory levels to meet corporate goals. Review and understand gaps between forecast and budget and communicate these with key stakeholders. Ensure demand planning activities are undertaken in line with global standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the development, analysis and coordination of planning and supply chain reporting. Identify current and potential product shortages and excess inventory. Review stock to sales ratios and respond to changing sales trends&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide ad hoc reports to assist partners across International, Finance, Supply Chain, Sales and Marketing with ongoing management of their business areas. Support Supply Chain team with analytics pertaining to key demand and supply chain metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in monthly Sales, Inventory and Operations Planning functions - representing demand planning interests through report execution and contributing to review and action item discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track current and future inventory ownership for both finished goods and components based on purchasing plans and demand forecasts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide production forecasts beyond purchase orders to partners and CMs to provide transparency into future raw material needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute excess inventory management by identifying SKUs over target or with excess ownership based on expiration dates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications/Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in relevant field preferred or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of experience working in inventory control and planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consumer Packaged Goods Industry experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Excel, Google Sheets, and forecasting systems. ERP experience helpful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of inventory management practices and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong mathematical and analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent ability to prioritize, multitask, work independently and meet strict deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with budgeting, forecasting, and data analysis&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and oral communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hi, we’re Supergoop! Since 2005, we’ve been changing the way the world thinks about sunscreen. Today, we’re as committed as ever to creating feel-good sunscreen that you’ll really want to wear. Because protecting your skin’s health is what we’re all about. Every. Single. Day.™&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Supergoop! is on a mission to change the way the world thinks about sunscreen—and social is where that mission comes to life every day. We&#39;re looking for a Director of Social &amp;amp; Influencer Marketing who understands that we&#39;re not building a sunscreen feed; we&#39;re building a brand world where SPF feels effortless, joyful, and completely inseparable from real life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Social &amp;amp; Influencer Marketing will own the full content and social strategy—setting the vision for how Supergoop! shows up across owned channels, creator partnerships, and community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires someone who can hold the strategic thread across all of it: from the editorial calendar to the influencer tier strategy to the brand franchises that make Supergoop! unmistakable.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Social &amp;amp; Content Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the full content and social strategy for Supergoop! across Instagram, TikTok, and YouTube—setting the vision for how the brand shows up across every format, franchise, and moment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the VP to translate the brand messaging into a clear, consistent social point of view that drives both awareness and cultural relevance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a content system rooted in the duality of utility and wonder: content that earns daily trust and content that makes people stop scrolling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop long- and short-term roadmaps supporting hero franchise moments (Unseen, Play), key retail partnerships, and cultural platforms (PGA TOUR, Alterra, and beyond).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own platform strategy with clear channel roles—understanding what Instagram Feed, Reels, Stories, TikTok, and YouTube each uniquely do for the brand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a sharp read on the competitive landscape and ensure Supergoop! occupies the white space between expert authority and cultural relevance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Influencer &amp;amp; Community Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the influencer and community strategy as an integrated part of the broader content vision—ensuring creator content, organic community, and owned social feel like one cohesive brand world, not separate workstreams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the multi-tiered influencer strategy aligned with brand, product, partnership, and commercial priorities—defining the role of creators across the full funnel (awareness → consideration → conversion → loyalty).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the Manager of Influencer Marketing on paid creator strategy, campaign execution, and performance optimization; guide the Manager of Community Engagement on organic creator relationships, UGC, and social listening.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop long-term ambassador programs and brand-building paid partnerships; oversee negotiations and contracts with creators and agencies as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify cultural moments, platform shifts, and audience signals worth acting on—and know which ones to let pass.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the habit-driving content systems—reminders, rituals, relatable moments—that move people from aware to loyal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Leadership &amp;amp; Cross-Functional Partnership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead two direct reports—Manage

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hi, we’re Supergoop! Since 2005, we’ve been changing the way the world thinks about sunscreen. Today, we’re as committed as ever to creating feel-good sunscreen that you’ll really want to wear. Because protecting your skin’s health is what we’re all about. Every. Single. Day.™&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supergoop! is seeking a highly motivated and detail-oriented Wholesale Operations Manager to join our team. In this role, you will own the end-to-end execution of wholesale order fulfillment with a particular focus on our largest retail partners - Target and Ulta Beauty. You will serve as the operational backbone for these accounts, managing everything from warehouse scheduling and order flow to partner communication and process improvement. You will report directly to the VP, Operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role &amp;amp; Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary operations point of contact for Supergoop&#39;s Target and Ulta Beauty account managers, managing order execution, compliance requirements, and retailer-specific workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Sales and Finance-owned demand planning teams to translate forecasts into actionable fulfillment plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate demand signals into warehouse scheduling, ensuring capacity is allocated appropriately across retail account windows and promotional events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the full wholesale fulfillment cycle, from order receipt and prioritization through pick, pack, and shipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review wholesale orders against available inventory and provide timely, accurate guidance on fulfillment timelines and any adjustments needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with 3PL and warehouse partners on inbound scheduling, outbound prioritization, and labor planning to meet retailer compliance windows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear and proactive communication with wholesale partners on order status, shipment details, and any exceptions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and flag inventory risk — stockouts, shorts, aged inventory — and partner with Purchasing and Inventory Control on resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and drive process improvements that increase efficiency, accuracy, and compliance across the wholesale fulfillment operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data and operational tools - including AI-powered platforms such as Claude, Parabola, and others - to automate workflows, analyze fulfillment performance, and surface insights that&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications/Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3–5 years of experience in wholesale operations, retail fulfillment, or a distribution environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct experience managing major retail accounts such as Target, Ulta Beauty, Sephora, or similar — familiarity with their compliance and routing requirements strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of warehouse operations, inventory management, and order management systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with EDI, WMS, and ERP platforms (NetSuite experience a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to use technology to improve operational workflows; experience with AI tools such as Claude, Parabola, or similar platforms is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to act quickly on data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communicator — able to manage retailer relationships, internal cross-functional partners, and 3PL contacts simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized, self-directed, and able to manage multiple priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
