&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hi, we’re Supergoop! Since 2005, we’ve been changing the way the world thinks about sunscreen. Today, we’re as committed as ever to creating feel-good sunscreen that you’ll really want to wear. Because protecting your skin’s health is what we’re all about. Every. Single. Day.™&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a highly organized and resourceful professional who thrives in a dynamic, people-first environment. You bring a strong sense of ownership to your work — anticipating needs, solving problems proactively, and ensuring that both the office and the people within it operate at their best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are an effective communicator who can engage confidently across all levels of an organization, from first-time visitors to senior executives. You understand the importance of discretion, professionalism, and attention to detail — especially when supporting leadership. Above all, you are someone who takes pride in creating an environment where others can do their best work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role &amp;amp; Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of office operations and executive support. Reporting to the CEO’s Executive Assistant, this role serves as a key resource for both the day-to-day function of our office and the administrative needs of our leadership team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Office Management &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, organized, and well-stocked office environment that reflects Supergoop!&#39;s vibrant brand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage office inventory, including supplies, snacks, and equipment; anticipate needs before they become problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place and track orders; restock and organize supplies as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with vendors for office services, maintenance, and deliveries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure common areas, kitchens, and conference rooms are tidy, functional, and guest-ready at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve office systems and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reception &amp;amp; Guest Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the first point of contact for all visitors, couriers, and guests — setting a warm, professional tone from the moment they walk in&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Greet and assist guests, ensuring a seamless and welcoming experience that reflects our company culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage incoming and outgoing mail and packages, including logging and routing as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee conference room scheduling and setup, ensuring spaces are properly arranged and equipped&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal meetings with logistics coordination (room prep, AV setup, refreshments, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Administrative Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide calendar support for several executives, including scheduling meetings, managing conflicts, and coordinating across time zones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise closely with the CEO&#39;s Executive Assistant to align calendars and scheduling across the Executive Leadership Team (ELT)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with meeting coordination and logistics, including preparing materials, taking notes, or arranging travel when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support ad hoc administrative tasks and special projects as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle sensitive information with a high degree of professionalism and discretion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications/Experience &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of experience in an office coordinator, admin

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hi, we’re Supergoop! Since 2005, we’ve been changing the way the world thinks about sunscreen. Today, we’re as committed as ever to creating feel-good sunscreen that you’ll really want to wear. Because protecting your skin’s health is what we’re all about. Every. Single. Day.™&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supergoop! is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Retail Marketing Manager &lt;/strong&gt;to help bring new product launches &amp;amp; marketing campaigns to life across key retailers in North America (Sephora, Nordstrom, Bluemercury, and priority Indie accounts). This includes (but is not limited to!) merchandising, product messaging, IRL events, retail media, social media, and dotcom activations. This highly ambitious, creative, detail-oriented, and passionate individual should have their finger on the pulse of beauty, consumer-obsessed, love to make to-do lists &amp;amp; cross things off, and enjoy building relationships.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;360 Integrated Marketing:&lt;/strong&gt; In this role, you will own the development, execution, and reporting of all retail marketing programs that increase awareness, drive traffic, and convert shoppers across key accounts. You will spearhead execution of all marketing programs to support product launches and core campaigns that ladder up to global strategy and sales plan while meeting specific retailer needs. You will partner with internal accounts, events, education, social, and influencer teams to build calendar synergy and amplify retailer key moments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visual Merchandising:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead Visual Merchandising &amp;amp; Secondary Placement strategy across Sephora, Nordstrom, Bluemercury, and priority Indie accounts. Project manage to meet key deadlines while collaborating with Retailers, Account Management, and Creative to execute assortment, messaging, graphics, and proofing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sampling:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead sampling and co-op initiatives across all regions. Oversee execution of all sampling programs to ensure key dates are met&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dotcom&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own concepting and briefing asset deliverables and copy for all new launches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continued optimization of existing pages ensuring pages stay up to date with best in class assets to help grow our retailer.com business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and own deliverable tracker to ensure timelines meet key dates&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Meetings: &lt;/strong&gt;Help support team in preparation and execution of market weeks by building necessary materials and planning meeting logistics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage retail marketing budgets&lt;/strong&gt; including estimates, POs, and monthly reconciliations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop cross functional relationships&lt;/strong&gt; to ensure all deliverables are aligned with product launches, retailer timelines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cultivate strong relationships &lt;/strong&gt;with retail partners and key stakeholders to foster collaboration and maximize opportunities for brand exposure and growth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inspire! &lt;/strong&gt;Monitor industry developments, obsess over consumer trends, and have a steady pulse on store updates to inform / inspire retail marketing strategies and in store execution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will thrive in this role if you are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CREATIVE: You are innovative and embrace forward-thinking approaches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extremel

